<br>
Day in, Day out, I can see how some clerics just stop replying to rez requests. It gets very tiring to continually have someone else's death and xp loss become some psycho guilt trip and "your" fault. Am I sorry that Barbie died? Yes. Do I wish I had seen him fall earlier so I might have been of more assistance? Yes. Am I going to run back two zones, then run back to where I was for a person who is feeding me a line about their death being my responsibility/fault? Don't count on it.<br>
<br>
One more thing -<br>
You wrote:<br>
<i><br>
Now that day (Celestea mentioned) I zoned out of the Tower in iceclad, excepted I lagged and I was at full health when I left the tower and was at half a bub when i came out, sow didn't matter I was ran down within a few seconds. I was kind of mad I lost my lvl etc....... I explained this to the the cleric that just zoned out of the Tower... he ignored me..... I sent another tell... did a who all cleric 49 60 again and he was in EC... SO SHUT UP THAT IS BEING A JERK. </i><br>
<br>
So in the space of a few minutes he got from Tower to EC? Did you ever stop to consider he might have been porting with someone and never seen your original tell (there is a lag time when you are zoning in where tells go through but you don't see them) and that *gasp* he may have never even really noticed your body? He obviously didn't get to Ecommons that fast by running/the boat, so it's not like he just leisurely strolled around your corpse for an hour laughing at you.. As much as we forget, this game isn't about "ME ME ME" to anyone but us....and that fact doesn't make anyone a jerk. It's just the way the cards fall some days.<br>
<br>
**note, I took the Barb's name out of the log because a side effect of my rant the other day was that the druid who was the focus of it was suddenly in a new guild two days later, and I have this weird bit of guilt that somehow my rant caused that, something I had not intended. I was just blowing steam, not looking to get her axed from something. So in the future, I'll most likely be removing names from rants.<br>
